[normal]Mark Addison[bold]: 
[normal]Perhaps I can say a word or two. We are as frustrated as everybody else about this. As you know, we would like to have been in a position to move more quickly
[normal],
[normal] and the GMC is in a slightly different place. Perhaps I could just explain why. There are three fundamental issues that affect a regulator
[normal]’
[normal]s ability to test for language, as
[normal] I see it. One is the European d
[normal]irecti
[normal]ve. The second is the way that d
[normal]irective is transposed into UK law. The third is the legal framework that the regulator has. The GMC happened to have a legal framework 
[normal]which
[normal] has, I think, the 
[normal]“
[normal]licence to practise
[normal]”
[normal] component to it
