[normal] which allows them, with the right kind of signals from the Commission, if their legislation is tweaked,
[normal] to move to be able to language-
[normal]test. We are not in that posit
[normal]ion. First of all, the current d
[normal]irective is generally quite hostile. Second, the way it is transposed makes things difficult for us. Third, and most importantly, we do not have that distinction
[normal],
[normal] so we cannot introduce a point in the process between registration
[normal] and the right to practise that
[normal] will allow us t
[normal]o introduce a language test. That is the current position
[normal] unless there is a willingness on the Government
[normal]’s side
[normal] to introduce leg
[normal]islation that
[normal] would advance us to the point where
[normal] we could make that distinction.
[normal] 
[normal]T
[normal]hat would be a very big thing to ask in advance of the Law Commission coming through and in advance of the tra
[normal]nsposition of the new directive, which will help, 
[normal]which i
